    "spell": {
        "name": "Scrying",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "text": "You magically spy on a creature of your choice. Scrying works like *clairvoyance*, except that the image you receive is less precise, insufficient for *teleport* and similar spells. Instead of creating an eye in a set location within 500 feet, you instead create an eye that manifests just above the target. You can choose a target either by name or by touching one of its possessions or a piece of its body. If you haven't met the target in person, *scrying's* DC is 2 lower, and if you are unaware of the target's identity (perhaps because you found an unknown creature's fang at a crime scene), the DC is instead 10 lower.  \n  \n The effect of scrying depends on the target's Will save.",
        "subtype": "spell",
        "spell_type": "spell",
        "rank": 6,
        "traits": [
            {
